Mali-Guinea-France: Officials of the Mali Government reportedly have discovered a network organized by French military officers and African elements for smuggling arms from Mali to opponents of President Touré in Guinea. Mali officials are likely to regard such a discovery as confirmation of Touré's charges of a French-controlled plot against Guinea, and the sympathy of moderate Malians for France may be seriously weakened.

In Guinea, pro-Soviet elements are reported exploiting the alleged plot in an effort to draw Guinea closer to the bloc
